#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Aṭṭhasatapariyāyavagga"
msgstr "3. The Explanation of the Hundred and Eight"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 23. Aññatarabhikkhusutta → bhikkhusuttaṃ (bj) | bhikkhu (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Aññatarabhikkhusutta"
msgstr "23. With a Mendicant"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.23:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "sn36.23:1.2"
msgid ""
"“katamā nu kho, bhante, vedanā, katamo vedanāsamudayo, katamā "
"vedanāsamudayagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is feeling? What’s the origin of feeling? What’s the practice "
"that leads to the origin of feeling?"

msgctxt "sn36.23:1.3"
msgid "Katamo vedanānirodho, katamā vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"What’s the cessation of feeling? What’s the practice that leads to the "
"cessation of feeling?"

msgctxt "sn36.23:1.4"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr "And what is feeling’s gratification, drawback, and escape?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.23:2.1"
msgid "“Tisso imā, bhikkhu, vedanā—"
msgstr "“Mendicant, there are these three feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.2"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.3"
msgid "Imā vuccanti, bhikkhu, vedanā."
msgstr "These are called feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.4"
msgid "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo."
msgstr "Feeling originates from contact."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.5"
msgid "Taṇhā vedanāsamudayagāminī paṭipadā."
msgstr "Craving is the practice that leads to the origin of feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.6"
msgid "Phassanirodhā vedanānirodho."
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.7"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of feelings is simply this noble "
"eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.9"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ vedanāya assādo;"
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling: this is its "
"gratification."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.10"
msgid "yaṃ vedanā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ vedanāya ādīnavo;"
msgstr ""
"That feeling is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback."

msgctxt "sn36.23:2.11"
msgid ""
"yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Removing and giving up desire and greed for feeling: this is its escape.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.23:2.12"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
